Right.

110
00:07:10,034 --> 00:07:13,663
I left my home against my parents' wishes.

111
00:07:14,372 --> 00:07:16,457
I know they must be worried,

112
00:07:16,541 --> 00:07:19,710
so I want to put them at ease
by showing some results.

113
00:07:29,971 --> 00:07:31,764
"Say something."

114
00:07:31,847 --> 00:07:34,225
"Do you know how precious it was to me?"

115
00:07:34,308 --> 00:07:37,770
"It's a treasure from…"

116
00:07:37,853 --> 00:07:40,815
"It's a treasure I received
from someone dear to me."

117
00:07:41,524 --> 00:07:44,360
"It's a treasure I received
from someone dear to me."

118
00:07:47,863 --> 00:07:50,700
"What's with that attitude?
Say something."

119
00:07:50,783 --> 00:07:52,868
"Do you know how precious it was to me?"

120
00:07:53,452 --> 00:07:55,496
-Cheers!
-Cheers.

121
00:07:55,580 --> 00:08:00,376
I wanted more time to practice,
so I started work as a hostess.

122
00:08:00,459 --> 00:08:02,628
You're a heavy drinker, huh?

123
00:08:02,712 --> 00:08:03,629
Go for one more?

124
00:08:03,713 --> 00:08:05,548
-Sure.
-I'd love to.

125
00:08:06,340 --> 00:08:08,801
We've kept you waiting long enough.

126
00:08:08,884 --> 00:08:13,264
Now, we'll announce the winner
who passed the final review.

127
00:08:17,351 --> 00:08:23,232
The winner of the Kodama Productions
Next Star Audition 2020 is…

128
00:08:29,947 --> 00:08:31,532
Ms. Yuri Hara!

129
00:08:31,616 --> 00:08:33,034
Congratulations!

130
00:08:36,329 --> 00:08:38,372
Come to the center of the stage.

131
00:08:42,668 --> 00:08:44,337
It was my last chance.

132
00:08:45,463 --> 00:08:46,714
-Did you hear?
-What?

133
00:08:46,797 --> 00:08:48,382
That the audition was rigged.

134
00:08:48,466 --> 00:08:49,383
Seriously?

135
00:08:49,467 --> 00:08:53,888
Apparently, the agency did it
to get publicity for their talent's debut.

136
00:08:53,971 --> 00:08:56,682
I guess it's all about who you know, huh?

137
00:09:19,080 --> 00:09:21,499
And it was then of all times…

138
00:09:22,083 --> 00:09:23,125
