140
00:09:26,128 --> 00:09:27,838
I feel sorry for the wife.

141
00:10:20,599 --> 00:10:22,184
Why didn't you come?

142
00:10:53,841 --> 00:10:54,675
HEY, IT'S MARIKA

143
00:10:54,759 --> 00:10:57,636
WANT TO GET DRINKS WITH
HIDETA ASO FROM KODAMA PRODUCTIONS?

144
00:10:57,720 --> 00:10:58,888
GOOD NETWORKING CHANCE!

145
00:11:03,184 --> 00:11:04,935
Try it sometime.

146
00:11:05,019 --> 00:11:07,980
-Can you keep going?
-Of course. We just got started.

147
00:11:09,398 --> 00:11:11,400
You're good with your drinks, I see.

148
00:11:11,484 --> 00:11:12,693
I like that.

149
00:11:12,776 --> 00:11:14,737
-So, where are you from?
-Kyoto.

150
00:11:14,820 --> 00:11:16,113
Wait, me too!

151
00:11:16,197 --> 00:11:17,698
-Really?
-Yeah, really.

152
00:11:17,781 --> 00:11:21,327
-Not just trying to hit on her?
-No, I'm being for real right now.

153
00:11:31,504 --> 00:11:34,423
SORRY, SOMETHING CAME UP,
SO I CAN'T MAKE IT.

154
00:11:45,017 --> 00:11:46,060
Enjoying yourself?

155
00:11:47,061 --> 00:11:47,895
Mr. Aso.

156
00:11:48,646 --> 00:11:49,522
Are you alone?

157
00:11:50,189 --> 00:11:51,190
Care to join me?

158
00:11:52,525 --> 00:11:53,442
Yes.

159
00:11:56,737 --> 00:12:00,032
So you quit high school
and moved to Tokyo alone?

160
00:12:00,950 --> 00:12:01,867
Yes.

161
00:12:02,660 --> 00:12:06,580
My parents opposed it,
so I basically ran away from home.

162
00:12:08,332 --> 00:12:10,918
But things haven't gone well since then.

163
00:12:14,880 --> 00:12:19,051
I actually took an audition
for your agency recently.

164
00:12:19,134 --> 00:12:20,386
For us?

165
00:12:20,469 --> 00:12:21,387
Yes.

166
00:12:22,346 --> 00:12:25,224
But I didn't make it past the final stage.

167
00:12:26,642 --> 00:12:31,647
I decided to come here today
because I thought I could get to meet you,

168
00:12:31,730 --> 00:12:34,984
and ask what you think I'm lacking.

169
00:12:37,152 --> 00:12:39,905
Maybe the judges just lacked taste.

170
00:12:42,408 --> 00:12:44,702
You have a lot of charm, if you ask me.

171
00:12:47,955 --> 00:12:50,249
I can hear you out if you want.

172
00:12:52,334 --> 00:12:53,794
Will you really?

173
00:12:53,877 --> 00:12:57,214
Mr. Aso, we'll be leaving first then.

174
00:12:58,966 --> 00:13:00,092
Thank you.

175
00:13:00,175 --> 00:13:01,385
Take care.

176
00:13:01,468 --> 00:13:02,636
See you again.

177
00:13:07,057 --> 00:13:08,350
How about another drink?

178
00:13:09,351 --> 00:13:10,227
What?

179
00:13:10,311 --> 00:13:11,895
Or will you go home?

180
00:13:13,564 --> 00:13:14,690
I'm fine either way.

181
00:13:17,693 --> 00:13:18,611
How about it?

182
00:13:20,904 --> 00:13:23,949
I'll stay. I want to talk more with you.

183
00:13:25,284 --> 00:13:26,201
Come with me then.

184
00:13:56,732 --> 00:13:58,067
Thank you.

185
00:13:58,150 --> 00:13:59,068
Cheers.

186
00:13:59,151 --> 00:14:00,027
Cheers.

187
00:14:10,663 --> 00:14:11,664
Here.

188
00:14:11,747 --> 00:14:13,123
Thank you.

189
00:14:38,023 --> 00:14:40,818
Sorry, I think I drank too much.

190
00:14:49,243 --> 00:14:51,620
Wait. Stop it!

191
00:14:51,704 --> 00:14:53,372
That hurt.

192
00:14:54,415 --> 00:14:57,584
I'm sorry. But that's not why I…

193
00:14:57,668 --> 00:14:58,877
Just leave then.

194
00:15:01,588 --> 00:15:04,008
If that's the extent of your resolve.

195
00:15:11,056 --> 00:15:12,349
Just kidding.

196
00:15:13,392 --> 00:15:16,228
I'm willing to help you out, you know.

197
00:15:16,895 --> 00:15:19,273
I can connect you to the right people.

198
00:15:55,726 --> 00:15:57,895
I'm leaving first, okay?

199
00:15:57,978 --> 00:15:59,438
Have a shoot to get to.

200
00:16:01,065 --> 00:16:02,733
Here's your taxi fare.

201
00:16:03,442 --> 00:16:04,485
Bye.

202
00:16:09,198 --> 00:16:10,449
Goodbye.

203
00:16:18,165 --> 00:16:19,792
"Goodbye"?

204
00:17:04,711 --> 00:17:05,963
I'm fine.

205
00:17:09,967 --> 00:17:10,926
I'm fine.

206
00:17:15,347 --> 00:17:16,473
I'm fine.

207
00:17:20,727 --> 00:17:21,770
I'm fine…

208
00:17:23,605 --> 00:17:25,774
I'm fine.

209
00:17:30,904 --> 00:17:34,199
Over and over, I tried to convince myself.

210
00:17:34,283 --> 00:17:35,242
I'm fine.

211
00:17:36,285 --> 00:17:37,327
I'm fine.

212
00:17:39,037 --> 00:17:42,499
If I didn't do so, I thought I might snap.

213
00:17:44,293 --> 00:17:48,672
In the end, neither Aso nor
Kodama Productions ever contacted me.

214
00:17:50,048 --> 00:17:51,758
I had to face the reality.

215
00:17:55,721 --> 00:17:56,722
I was…

216
00:17:58,056 --> 00:18:02,269
My dream was taken advantage of.

217
00:18:03,770 --> 00:18:06,982
I was just used by him…

218
00:18:07,900 --> 00:18:11,236
as an outlet for his sexual desires.

219
00:18:13,238 --> 00:18:16,408
That was five years ago.

220
00:18:19,411 --> 00:18:21,413
Let's take a break.

221
00:18:22,623 --> 00:18:24,124
Please let me continue.

222
00:18:24,666 --> 00:18:26,627
-But--
-I want to tell you.

223
00:18:27,294 --> 00:18:28,337
All of it.

224
00:18:30,839 --> 00:18:32,799
Tell me if it gets too much.

225
00:18:36,637 --> 00:18:38,722
Did you ask anyone for help?

226
00:18:41,099 --> 00:18:44,811
I told my agency about it,
and they let me go the next day.

227
00:18:45,479 --> 00:18:46,313
What?

228
00:18:46,939 --> 00:18:48,190
My manager said,

229
00:18:49,149 --> 00:18:52,945
"Don't drag us into this. We don't want
any issues with Kodama Productions."

230
00:18:53,028 --> 00:18:54,321
As he yelled at me.

231
00:18:56,156 --> 00:19:00,410
"Sexual assault? You just tried
to seduce him and failed, didn't you?"

232
00:19:02,287 --> 00:19:04,873
I thought, "Oh, I see."

233
00:19:05,582 --> 00:19:07,626
"I guess that wasn't sexual assault."

234
00:19:08,710 --> 00:19:11,380
"It's just an excuse
that I couldn't fight back."

235
00:19:11,463 --> 00:19:14,174
"It was my fault for going to the party

236
00:19:14,258 --> 00:19:18,971
and trying to get close to him,
so I could get more work."

237
00:19:20,347 --> 00:19:22,140
"It was all my fault."

238
00:19:22,224 --> 00:19:23,392
"I deserved it."

239
00:19:24,559 --> 00:19:26,478
"So there was nothing to be done."

240
00:19:28,522 --> 00:19:29,898
Did you try the police?

241
00:19:32,818 --> 00:19:33,777
I couldn't.

242
00:19:34,945 --> 00:19:36,738
I thought they wouldn't bother.

243
00:19:40,075 --> 00:19:46,248
But as time went on,
I started to feel detached from it.

244
00:19:47,165 --> 00:19:51,044
It started to feel less real,
almost like it was a bad dream.

245
00:19:52,921 --> 00:19:54,381
What was I fussing over?

246
00:19:55,007 --> 00:19:56,883
I'm totally fine now.

247
00:20:00,095 --> 00:20:03,056
I probably looked normal to others.

248
00:20:04,975 --> 00:20:08,395
But for that entire period,

249
00:20:09,229 --> 00:20:13,442
I wasn't even sure
whether I was alive or dead.

250
00:20:14,860 --> 00:20:18,530
Everything felt so dull,
no matter what I did.

251
00:20:18,613 --> 00:20:20,824
-That'll be 2,700 yen.
-Okay.

252
00:20:22,826 --> 00:20:27,456
